title: Grateful Dead Live at Nassau Coliseum on 1992-03-11
description: Cold Rain & Snow, Victim Or The Crime, Dire Wolf, Queen Jane Approximately, Althea, It's All Over Now, So Many Roads, Picasso Moon China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Playin' In The Band-> Terrapin Station-> Drums-> Jam-> The Last Time-> Black Peter-> Around & Around, E: Knockin' On Heaven's Door

reviews.review_text:
a show for the bubble this was a pretty good and solid show. not the best of the tour, but not the worst. a friend of mine, who had another friend who was paralized from the neck down ( i'm sure some of you might have seen him at shows throughout the years ) passed away a short time before this 92 spring tour and, well, did anyone who was there notice the " red cross " symbol above the drum set? i was told that the second set was for brian. not sure if this is true, but looking at the set list, it was most of his fav tunes, and the black peter, knockin 4 the encore said a lot. it felt like the dead were giving their condolences to brian and all of his friends. i felt this as soon as the show started and am very happy to have a SBD that sounds crisp and clear. if yall ever saw brian in the van we all called the bubble, then you know what i'm sayin. he was in a wheelchair, and usually being pushed by my friend frankie. just thought i would pass on some info about what the 3-11-92 show might have been about. the set list kinda says it all. thankyou archive,, thankyou taper, and most of all, thankyou grateful dead.

cold night boy was it windy out, before this show.

t. station>drums>space is really unique.  terrapin station has an awesome jam and the soundboard is really nice.  I had listened to the beginning of ts from an aud recording.  really great recording but can hear the crazy guitar sounds quite as well.  a martix blend of this how would be a great project for someone.  after reading the comments the show also comes alive-the guy who was in a wheelchair having the second set possibly dedicated to him adds some nice thoughts.  I give it a 4.959 stars.  the sound on the space is great great dumming.   only thing better would to have been there.  I am going to examine more shows from 92.

My second show. As I remember it from my (poor) seat at Nassau Coliseum, this show was somewhat disappointing. My first show being 6-16-91 at Giants Stadium, I guess it's no surprise. That show melted my face, and showed me something I previously hadn't known. As I listen today I hear a spirited performance. For the transfer I'd ordinarily score this a three, but will give it four for two reasons. I was there, and this is the only soundboard copy at the Archive (or so I can see). Thank you for preserving this special moment in my life. Archive.org rocks.

-q :)
